            <p class="eyebrow">FAQs</p>
            <h2>Driveway drain cleaning FAQs</h2>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-list">
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">How often should driveway drains be cleaned?</button><div><p>Most residential driveway drains should be cleaned at least once a year — ideally in the spring after snowmelt and debris accumulation. Properties with heavy tree cover or driveways that collect significant sediment may need twice-annual service.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Can you clean drains that are completely blocked?</button><div><p>Yes. We use professional vacuum equipment for basin debris and high-pressure hydro jetting for blocked outlet lines. For severe blockages, we camera the line to identify the obstruction and determine the best approach.</p></div></div>
            <div class="faq-item"><button type="button" aria-expanded="false">What if the outlet line is damaged or collapsed?</button><div><p>If camera inspection reveals a damaged or collapsed outlet line, we provide a flat-rate repair quote. Most driveway drain outlet repairs involve replacing a short section of pipe and can be completed in a single visit.</p></div></div>
